elements index index Element
index &index.purpose;
&index.synopsis.gen; Description
An Index contains the formatted index of a document. An index may begin with introductory material, followed by any number of IndexEntrys or IndexDivs.
Processing expectations
&format.block; An Index in a Book frequently causes a forced page break in print media.
In many processing systems, indexes are generated automatically or semiautomatically and never appear instantiated as DocBook markup.
&FutureChanges;
DocBook DTDChanges for V5.0
Formal objects and other elements inappropriate for an index will be removed the content that can appear before the first IndexDiv or IndexEntry.
&index.parents.gen; &index.children.gen;
